            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">If you plan to use your UK Limited Company to open a bank account in your home country, sign corporate agreements, or register foreign branches, local authorities will require verified documents. An apostille certificate confirms that your UK incorporation documents are authentic and legally recognized under the Hague Convention.</p>
